  "Question": "<p>I want to show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_76\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\limits_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx=1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>.</p> <p>By definition <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_77\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\limits_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx=\\lim\\limits_{t\\to\\infty}\\int% \\limits_{-t}^{t}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits=\"false\">lim</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></munder><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow><mi>t</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> and since the integrand <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_78\"><math alttext=\"e^{-\\pi x^{2}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup></semantics></math></span> is an even function <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_79\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\limits_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx=\\lim\\limits_{t\\to\\infty}\\int% \\limits_{-t}^{t}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx=2\\lim\\limits_{t\\to\\infty}\\int\\limits_{0}^{t}e% ^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits=\"false\">lim</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></munder><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow><mi>t</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits=\"false\">lim</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></munder><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> i.e. we can equivalently show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_80\"><math alttext=\"\\lim\\limits_{t\\to\\infty}\\int\\limits_{0}^{t}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx=\\frac{1}{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits=\"false\">lim</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></munder><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span>.</p> <p>Since the antiderivative of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_81\"><math alttext=\"e^{-x^{2}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></msup></semantics></math></span> is given by the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Error_function\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">error function</a> we can't straightforwardly evaluate the integral, so I tried to use the power series expansion, hoping to be able to see that the resulting series will converge to <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_82\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></semantics></math></span>:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_83\"><math alttext=\"|\\int\\limits_{0}^{t}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx-\\frac{1}{2}|=|\\int\\limits_{0}^{t}\\sum% \\limits_{n=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{\\pi^{n}\\cdot x^{2n}}{n!}dx-\\frac{1}{2}|=|\\sum% \\limits_{n=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{\\pi^{n}\\cdot t^{2n+1}}{n!\\cdot(n+1)}-\\frac{1}{2}|\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></munderover><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>\u03c0</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>\u22c5</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>\u03c0</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>\u22c5</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow><mo>\u22c5</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>However, I'm in a doubt that it converges and a quick check in Wolfram Mathematica shows indeed that with <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_84\"><math alttext=\"t\\to\\infty\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span> the resulting series will diverge.</p> <p>What am I doing wrong? Can anybody help me with a proof for this problem? Any help will be really appreciated.</p>",
  "Title": "Show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_75\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\limits_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{-\\pi x^{2}}dx=1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>",
  "Tags": "calculus,integration,improper-integrals"
